body:
Currently it seems that the only way to silence an `unreachable_code` warning is via an interior `#![allow(unreachable_code)]` attribute that would apply to the entire scope or artificially creating a new scope with the inner attribute in question.

Would it be possible to allow a control flow statement to be individually tagged with a regular `#[allow(unreachable_code)]` statement to also suffice?

e.g. the following should not emit a warning about unreachable code:

```rust
pub fn foo() -> u32 {
    #[allow(unreachable_code)]
    return 0;

    let foo = 7;
    return foo;
}
```

[playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&code=pub%20fn%20foo()%20-%3E%20u32%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20%23%5Ballow(unreachable_code)%5D%0A%20%20%20%20return%200%3B%0A%0A%20%20%20%20let%20foo%20%3D%207%3B%0A%20%20%20%20return%20foo%3B%0A%7D%0A)
